   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The raw series is non-stationary. The ADF test fails to reject the unit root (p = 0.85), and the KPSS test rejects level-stationarity (p = 0.01). Both tests agree the series needs differencing. A seasonal difference (D=1) brings the series closer to stationarity.\n",
    "\n",
    "After both first and seasonal differencing (d=1, D=1), the ADF strongly rejects the unit root. The ACF on the double-differenced series shows a significant spike at lag 1 and at lag 12, with rapid decay elsewhere. The PACF shows a spike at lag 1 and at seasonal lags. Combined with the EACF table, candidate nonseasonal orders include AR(1), AR(2), or MA(1), and the seasonal component points toward SMA(1). This suggests ARIMA(1,1,0)(0,1,1,12) or ARIMA(2,1,0)(0,1,1,12) as starting points."
   ]
