    "The CV results across all full-data models show similar RMSE values, with ARIMA and Airline slightly ahead of ETS and STL+ETS. However, all of these models share a fundamental issue: they learn from the entire 2016 to 2024 series, which is dominated by a strong upward trend. When they forecast, they continue that trend. If the series is actually plateauing or has entered a new regime (as the 2024 internal test suggests), these models will systematically overshoot.\n",
