   "source": [
    "The rolling Chow test identifies **April 2020** as the most significant structural break in the series (F = 7.83, p < 0.001). The period from January through June 2020 is consistently significant at the 1% level, coinciding exactly with the onset of COVID-19 disruptions. Dates before October 2019 are not significant at the 5% level, confirming that the pre-2020 series follows a single regime.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Zivot-Andrews unit root test with intercept and trend break corroborates this finding, identifying **March 2020** as the structural break date. While the ZA test does not reject the unit root even after accounting for the break (consistent with the high persistence we observe in this series), the break date identification independently confirms the regime change.\n",
    "\n",
    "These formal tests provide statistical evidence supporting what the visual analysis suggested: the COVID-19 pandemic created a structural shift in the US retail job openings series. This motivates restricting the training window to the post-break regime."
