    "## Forecast Combination\n\nThe M-competition literature consistently finds that simple averages of 3+ diverse model families outperform individual models, particularly when no single model clearly dominates. With structural break uncertainty, mixed diagnostics, and ETS outperforming SARIMA on the internal holdout, no model has an unambiguous claim to being \"best.\" This is exactly the scenario where forecast combination adds value.\n\nWe combine three models from distinct families with equal weights:\n1. **SARIMA(1,0,0)(1,0,1,12)** (autoregressive, ARIMA family)\n2. **STL+AR(1)** (decomposition-based)\n3. **Fourier(K=4)+AR(1)** (regression-based seasonal)"
